sections.heading: Overview
content:
Janice E. Williams, PhD, MPH, was a postdoctoral fellow at the University of
North Carolina in Chapel Hill when she conducted her study on anger and heart
attack risk. She is currently a research epidemiologist at the U.S. Centers for
Disease Control and Prevention in Atlanta, Ga.
